23 Apr 2009 07:56






From chat about SCP-627:

: …Right. Google the trinity site.

: There are pics.

: Of EXACTLY how it turned out.

: Let me explain. Nukes work on normal science, it's true. Problem was, building them is HARD, and we needed something to make our initial tests work.

: The official story is that the first test nuke was a triumph of last-minute science go-get-'em attitude.

: What if it was something more… well, different.

: The other two worked as publicized, yes.

: But that first one? The dawn of the reign of terror that is the nuclear weapon?

: It was SCP-627 that gave it birth.

: And think about THIS… Compared to the other shit we have? We think it's "safe".

: It fits in beautifully with my views of the Foundation, hands everywhere, toying with all sorts of things, trying to keep the world from realizing that the laws of nature they know are just pretty wallpaper hastily applied over a chaotic and ruinous nightmare of reality.







